Pretoria - Justice and Correctional Services Minister Michael Masutha has appointed the Regional Commissioner of Gauteng, Zach Modise, as Acting National Commissioner of Correctional Services. Minister Masutha has congratulated Modise and wished him well in his new responsibility at the helm of Correctional Services. The minister has also thanked the Chief Operations Officer, Nontsikelelo Jolingana, for her contribution while acting as National Commissioner since 9 September 2013. Modise has already assumed his new duties. He has since appointed the Area Commissioner of the Johannesburg Management Area, Mandla Mkabela, as Acting Regional Commissioner for the Gauteng Region. Director Errol Korabie was appointed to act as the Area Commissioner of Johannesburg until further notice. â€“ SAnews.gov.za